Virtuals is Taking Over  Previously, Virtuals has only tapped into a $5-7BN market, taking >80% of AI Agent market share on Base. It essentially consolidated and channeled the demand for building and speculating on AI agents into one ecosystem of  @virtuals_io .  Expanding to Solana will allow Virtuals to tap into an additional $7-10BN AI agent market filled with retail interest and participationâ€”larger demand, larger volume, much more excitement, and a wide variety of cultures (frameworks, unique agents, infrastructure, and more).  Value Accrual of $VIRTUAL will be twofold: -  @solana  offers a significantly better trading experience compared to EVM: no need to sign authorizations multiple times, smooth UI/UX with its high throughput, and low fees.  -  @MeteoraAG ''s DLMM includes features like zero-slippage bins, dynamic fees, and flexible liquidity shapes. These enable better capital efficiency, mitigate IL, and incentivize more liquidity provisioning activity, resulting in a better trading and LPâ€™ing environment for investors.  - The AGENT/VIRTUAL flywheel further expands, enabling higher value capture with $VIRTUAL token. More teams will need to buy $VIRTUAL to set up LPs, while speculators buy $VIRTUAL to start trading agent tokens.  - Strategic SOL Reserve (1%) will likely offer a flywheel effect similar to what weâ€™ve seen recently, where ~13M $VIRTUAL was used to buy back & burn agent tokens. We could see a similar scenario here in the future, with the reserve accelerating development on Virtuals agents on Solana.  To top it off, the team is kickstarting an initiative to attract builders by running the Virtuals AI Hackathon in partnership with  @SolanaFndn  with 42K $VIRTUAL incentives  Weâ€™ve seen how Solana AI Hackathons play out with  @sendaifun , and the quality of builders coming out of these programs is nothing short of impressive.  Collectively, Solana AI Hackathon participants are now valued at $450M in market cap combinedâ€”and this is only from 1/3 of the total projects that launched a token. Meanwhile, 222 projects have yet to launch (source:  @GoatIndexAI ).  Agent-to-Agent interactions / Agent Businesses (aka Virtuals Society) has been the core focus of the ecosystemâ€”the ability for agents to generate greater value, far greater than the sum of their parts.  Weâ€™re starting to see this unfold with examples like: â€¢  @luna_virtuals  tasking an NFT agent to create NFT art, â€¢  @luna_virtuals  ordering food via  @Byte__AI  for  @jessepollak , â€¢  @santavirtuals  utilizing  @questflow â€™s MAOP to distribute incentives across Virtuals.  As the Virtuals nation expands, the network of quality, value-adding agents grows exponentially. This will unlock a far greater variety of unique use cases generated through interactions between agents (on Base & Solana). A small economy transforms into one 100x larger, with  @virtuals_io  firmly positioned as the Coordination Layer at its core.  And the team isnâ€™t stopping with Solanaâ€”more is incoming, as seen from the recent integration with  @LayerZero_Core .  Just as Trump catalyzed the birth of America, the AI & Crypto Nation,  This marks the birth of Virtuals, the AI Agent Nation.
